# {{.ProjectName}}

> Built with the **GOTH** stack: **G**o · **templ** · **HTMX** · **Tailwind**

## Setup

Copy the example env file and fill in your values:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Then run:

```bash
make setup   # downloads HTMX, Alpine, builds Tailwind
make dev     # starts Air live-reload dev server
```

## Environment variables

| Variable | Default (dev) | Description |
|----------|--------------|-------------|
| `DB_PATH` | `./internal/data/database.db` | SQLite database path |
| `PORT` | `3060` | HTTP listen port |
| `ENV` | *(unset)* | Set to `production` for JSON logging |

## Development

```bash
make dev          # live reload (air + templ + tailwind watchers)
make build        # production binary
make clean        # remove temp files and generated Go code
```

## Database

```bash
make backup       # timestamped backup → backups/
make restore      # interactively restore a backup
make db-optimize  # VACUUM & ANALYZE
make db-shell     # SQLite shell with pretty-printing
```

## Deploy

The Makefile includes a commented-out remote deploy section (Pi / VPS) using
`rsync` and `sqlite3_rsync` for safe database sync. Fill in `REMOTE_USER`,
`REMOTE_HOST`, and `REMOTE_DIR` at the top of the Makefile and uncomment the
targets to enable:

```bash
make deploy          # cross-compile + rsync binary to remote
make logs            # tail remote log
make status          # service status, DB size, disk usage
make db-push         # push local DB to remote
make db-pull         # pull remote DB locally (as database.debug.db)
make db-shell-remote # SQLite shell on remote database
make bench           # disk write benchmark on remote
```

